In[240]:
n_clusters = [3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10]
X = np.array(data_scaled)

for K in n_clusters:
    
    fig, ax1 = plt.subplots()
    fig.set_size_inches(18, 7)
    model = KMeans(n_clusters = K, random_state = 10)
    cluster_labels = model.fit_predict(X)
    silhouette_avg = silhouette_score(X, cluster_labels)
    sample_silhouette_values = silhouette_samples(X, cluster_labels)

    y_lower = 10
    for i in range(K):
    
        ith_cluster_silhouette_values = sample_silhouette_values[cluster_labels == i]
        
        ith_cluster_silhouette_values.sort()
    
        size_cluster_i = ith_cluster_silhouette_values.shape[0]
        y_upper = y_lower + size_cluster_i

        color = cm.nipy_spectral(float(i) / K)
        ax1.fill_betweenx(np.arange(y_lower, y_upper),
                          0, ith_cluster_silhouette_values,
                          facecolor=color, edgecolor=color, alpha=0.7)
        ax1.text(-0.05, y_lower + 0.5 * size_cluster_i, str(i))
        y_lower = y_upper + 10 

    # set the axes and plot label
    ax1.set_title("Silhouette Plot")
    ax1.set_xlabel("Silhouette coefficient")
    ax1.set_ylabel("Cluster label")

    ax1.axvline(x=silhouette_avg, color="red", linestyle="--")
    ax1.set_yticks([])  
    ax1.set_xticks([-0.1, 0, 0.2, 0.4, 0.6, 0.8])

    colors = cm.nipy_spectral(cluster_labels.astype(float) / K)
    
    # set the common title for subplots
    plt.suptitle(("Silhouette Analysis for K-Means Clustering with n_clusters = %d" % K), fontsize=14, 
                 fontweight='bold')

# display the plot
plt.show()

Apply KMeans on PCA components

In[249]:
inertias = []
sil_scores = []

K_range = range(2, 10)
for k in K_range:
    km = KMeans(n_clusters=k, random_state=42)
    labels = km.fit_predict(data_pca)
    inertias.append(km.inertia_)
    sil_scores.append(silhouette_score(data_pca, labels))

print(" the silhouette score is: \n", sil_scores)

# Plot elbow and silhouette
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))

plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
plt.plot(K_range, inertias, marker='o')
plt.title('KMeans Elbow Method')
plt.xlabel('Number of clusters')
plt.ylabel('Inertia')

plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
plt.plot(K_range, sil_scores, marker='o')
plt.title('KMeans Silhouette Scores')

plt.ylabel('Silhouette Score')
plt.show()

# Using KNN to estimate the eps value for DBSCAN
min_samples = 20
neighbors = NearestNeighbors(n_neighbors=min_samples)
neighbors_fit = neighbors.fit(data_pca)
distances, indices = neighbors_fit.kneighbors(data_pca)


k_distances = np.sort(distances[:, -1])


plt.figure(figsize=(8, 4))

Conclusion

1. Data Preparation: Missing data are filled with Zeros and non-significant feature like 'SEQN' and feature with more than 50% missing values are removed.

2. Scaling: MinMaxScaler is used to bring all data within range

3. Clustering: KMeans is applied on scaled data using calculation methods - elbow and silhouette score and visualized.

( we observed good elbow bend for k = 5 and good score around 0.28)

4. Reduction technique with PCA: feature reducted to 45 with 95% of variance captured.

5. DBSCAN: Hyperparameter with eps = 4 and min sample = 50 resulted in 4 clusters with silhouette score of 0.319 and noise 1
